---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { DOMAIN } from '../../data/site';

const title = "Should I Cut or Bulk? The Ultimate Strategy Guide | BodyCompOS";
const description = "An evidence-based decision matrix to help you choose between fat loss (cutting) and muscle building (bulking) based on body fat percentage, lifting history, and metabolic baseline.";
const canonical = `${DOMAIN}/guides/should-i-cut-or-bulk`;

const schema = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'Article',
	headline: title,
	description: description,
	datePublished: '2026-06-25',
	dateModified: '2026-06-25',
	author: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: 'BodyCompOS Editorial Board',
	},
	publisher: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: 'BodyCompOS',
		logo: {
			'@type': 'ImageObject',
			url: `${DOMAIN}/favicon.svg`,
		},
	},
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} schema={[schema]}>
	<section class="site-container py-10 sm:py-12">
		<!-- Breadcrumbs -->
		<nav class="flex mb-6 text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground gap-2" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
			<a class="hover:text-accent transition-colors" href="/">Home</a>
			<span>/</span>
			<a class="hover:text-accent transition-colors" href="/guides">Guides</a>
			<span>/</span>
			<span class="text-foreground">Cut or Bulk Guide</span>
		</nav>

		<!-- Content Hero -->
		<div class="max-w-3xl">
			<p class="eyebrow">Expert SEO Guide</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black leading-tight sm:text-5xl text-foreground">
				Should I Cut or Bulk? <br/>
				<span class="text-accent bg-gradient-to-r from-accent to-success bg-clip-text text-transparent">The Scientific Decision Matrix</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
				Choosing whether to focus on fat loss (cutting) or muscle hypertrophy (bulking) is the foundation of physical programming. This guide details the physiological thresholds, body fat indices, and training parameters that dictate your optimal pathway.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Main editorial body -->
		<div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px]">
			<div class="content-panel bg-card border border-border p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl">
				<div class="prose-lite space-y-8 text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
					
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">1. The Energy Balance Dilemma</h2>
						<p>
							Thermodynamic laws dictate that skeletal muscle synthesis (hypertrophy) is an energy-intensive process that is highly optimized in a caloric surplus. Conversely, adipose tissue reduction (lipolysis) requires a caloric deficit. Because these metabolic pathways have opposing energy requirements, attempting to pursue both simultaneously—known as body recomposition—is slow and generally reserved for specific populations.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3">
							To prevent getting stuck in a cycle of marginal progress, you must select a primary strategic bias based on your current physical baseline, insulin sensitivity, and training experience.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">2. Body Fat Decision Thresholds</h2>
						<p>
							Your starting body fat percentage is the most important variable. High body fat percentages skew nutrient partitioning: excess calories are more likely to be stored as additional adipose tissue rather than muscle due to lower insulin sensitivity. Conversely, low body fat percentages support muscle gain with minimal fat spillover.
						</p>
						
						<div class="my-5 overflow-x-auto">
							<table class="w-full text-left text-xs border-collapse">
								<thead>
									<tr class="border-b border-border bg-muted/40 font-semibold text-foreground">
										<th class="p-3">Sex</th>
										<th class="p-3">Body Fat %</th>
										<th class="p-3">Recommended Strategy</th>
										<th class="p-3">Caloric Bias</th>
									</tr>
								</thead>
								<tbody class="divide-y divide-border">
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Male</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-accent">> 15%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Cut / Fat Loss Phase</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">15% Calorie Deficit</td>
									</tr>
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Male</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-success">10% - 14%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Lean Bulk or Recomp</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">Maintenance to 8% Surplus</td>
									</tr>
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Male</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-accent">< 10%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Lean Bulk / Hypertrophy</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">8% to 12% Surplus</td>
									</tr>
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Female</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-accent">> 24%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Cut / Fat Loss Phase</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">15% Calorie Deficit</td>
									</tr>
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Female</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-success">18% - 23%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Lean Bulk or Recomp</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">Maintenance to 8% Surplus</td>
									</tr>
									<tr>
										<td class="p-3 font-bold text-foreground">Female</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono text-accent">< 18%</td>
										<td class="p-3">Lean Bulk / Hypertrophy</td>
										<td class="p-3 font-mono">8% to 12% Surplus</td>
									</tr>
								</tbody>
							</table>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">3. Training Experience Adjustments</h2>
						<p>
							Lifting experience, or training age, modifies these thresholds. Beginners (under one year of structured resistance training) possess a high sensitivity to training stimuli. This allows them to build muscle and lose fat at the same time, even in a moderate caloric deficit.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3">
							Advanced lifters, however, face biological limits. Muscle gains require dedicated, long-term caloric surpluses (lean bulks) of 6 to 12 months, followed by brief, controlled cuts to reduce accumulated fat.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">4. Reassessment Rules</h2>
						<p>
							Do not change your strategy based on weekly scale noise. Track your morning weight daily, calculate a rolling 7-day average, and reassess after 3-4 weeks. If cutting and weight stalls despite high adherence, reduce daily calories by 100-150 kcal or increase daily activity (NEAT). If bulking and weight is flat, increase caloric intake by 100-150 kcal.
						</p>
					</section>

					<!-- YMYL Disclaimer -->
					<div class="border-t border-border pt-6 text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">
						<p><strong>YMYL Disclaimer:</strong> The information in this guide is for educational purposes only. Body composition transformations involve metabolic changes. Individuals with a history of metabolic disease, eating disorders, or other clinical concerns should consult a medical professional before making significant changes to their diet or activity.</p>
					</div>

				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Sidebar -->
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="surface border border-border p-5 rounded-2xl">
					<h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-foreground">Strategic Tools</h3>
					<p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2">Use our interactive engine to analyze your metrics and choose your strategy.</p>
					<a href="/assess" class="button-primary w-full text-center text-xs mt-4 block">Run Strategy Finder</a>
				</div>

				<div class="surface border border-border p-5 rounded-2xl">
					<h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-foreground">Related Guides</h3>
					<div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-xs">
						<a href="/guides/body-recomposition" class="block text-accent hover:underline">Body Recomposition Science</a>
						<a href="/guides/protein-nutrition" class="block text-accent hover:underline">Optimal Protein Intake</a>
						<a href="/guides/body-fat-percentage" class="block text-accent hover:underline font-semibold">Navy Body Fat Method</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
